cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.AI 

This paper involves natural language processing and corpus analysis, which suggests it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of cosine similarity to analyze the argument-distributions of verbs suggests it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the focus on finance articles suggests it could belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
